		<title>An Exciting Change Brings CarolinaFest 2012 to Uptown Charlotte</title>
		<link>http://theppl.us/blog/1025</link>
		<comments>http://theppl.us/blog/1025#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 26 Jun 2012 22:16:28 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>Justin Ruckman</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Blog]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://theppl.us/?p=1025</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[The Charlotte in 2012 convention host committee opted to move the location of CarolinaFest 2012 to Tryon Street in Uptown Charlotte. The committee had originally decided to hold the event in the Charlotte Motor Speedway this year but they believe this new change better meets the needs of the community. Dan Murray, the executive director [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="attachment_1033" class="wp-caption aligncenter" style="width: 298px"><img class="size-full wp-image-1033" title="" src="http://theppl.us/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/image001.jpg" alt="" width="288" height="288" /><p class="wp-caption-text">Photo Property of CLT BLog</p></div>
<p>The Charlotte in 2012 convention host committee opted to move the location of CarolinaFest 2012 to Tryon Street in Uptown Charlotte. The committee had originally decided to hold the event in the Charlotte Motor Speedway this year but they believe this new change better meets the needs of the community.</p>
<p>Dan Murray, the executive director of the charlotte in 2012 host committee, listed a few of the benefits this new change will bring, during a press conference earlier this afternoon. Some of those benefits include more convenient transportation options as well as access to the caucus meetings that will be taking place in nearby locations. Dan Murray also believes hosting CarolinaFest 2012 in Uptown Charlotte will help local businesses that will be open to the public during the events.</p>
<p>For more information, visit   charlottein2012.com </p>
]]></content:encoded>
