			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>It&#8217;s 6 months until the DNC, and a year since The PPL started organizing.</p>
<p>Last night we had a big party at Packard Place to celebrate the moment, and to make some announcements, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>the hiring of Angela Gala to be our Operations Strategy lead</li>
<li>launch of arts &#038; culture initiatives</li>
<li>formation of our advisory board</li>
<li>public fundraising campaign kickoff</li>
<li>open volunteer opportunities</li>
</ul>
<p>… and last but not least: <a href="http://theppl.us/join-us"><strong>registration is now open!</strong></a> For the low early-admission price of $45, you can reserve your seat at The PPL&#8217;s coworking spaces in uptown Charlotte during the week of the DNC, Sep 1-7.</p>
<p>Here are some photos from the kickoff event courtesy Grant Baldwin &#038; Shawn Gentry, thanks to everyone that made it out!</p>

